main event: One object with a long greenish yellow tail was observed in La Creste, Gibraltar on December 18, 1957.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 10 minutes, but the object was observed for just 1 minute.The object appeared and stopped multiple times during its flight.The object emitted a green-yellow color covering 10 degrees of arc.It was noted that other sources indicated no missile activity in the area.The observation possibly relates to an astronomical meteor based on comments in the report.
sighted object: one object with a green-yellow tail
